The paper focuses on modeling the joint visual and audio components of a video signal, which is a common task in computer vision (CV) and signal processing (SD) research. The proposed method also involves learning a neural network representation, which is a common approach in machine learning (LG) research. The paper also discusses applications related to audio-visual action recognition (MM) and audio source separation (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.SD, followed by cs.MM, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
